data.title: Good place to eat.
data.text: My husband and I ate here at the hotel's suggestion after a pretty long day of driving. We went there because it was close. I would say it is pretty dark and seemed kind of loud but the food we got was good. Our server had gotten several customers so others stepped in and helped so the service was good. We would go there again.

data.title: More limited menu than I expected
data.text: The food was good, well prepared but the selection was far to limited. No fresh trout next to the Platte River? REALLY?

data.title: Disappointing diner experience
data.text: Slow service at dinner, food was mediocre at best.  Not a place for dinner that I would recommend.  No ambience at all.

data.title: It's in a bar
data.text: Good food with huge portions. Only one waitress when we were there but great service. Has pool tables and good variety on menu. Kind of dark. Tables are kind of high but also has lower tables. Nice place for dinner with friends.

data.title: Good offer
data.text: Good breakfast was included in room price. Evening meal had good offer on steaks and food was very good.

data.title: Run!
data.text: Not only is this not even decent bar food, but the server was so distracted by 'a cute guy' that she ignored me from the moment he walked in until I had to be a bit demanding.  Server acted as though I was putting her out by asking for another drink, etc.  I had the wings and had to send them back, not cooked through.  Run from this place!

data.title: Great Service, Great Food
data.text: The front desk manager referred me and I ended up eating both nights. I had the best pub burger ever. The atmosphere was also great and the staff was good too.

data.title: Good food bad service priced ok
data.text: Dukes food is very good. Price isn't bad for the portion size. The service though, leaves allot to be desired. Staying at the hotel, Dukes is very convenient for dinner, be for warned, the wait to be seated is long, even with empty tables. The waitress sits in the seat to take your order, the waiter couldn't tell three different customers what beers were available. 7 minutes after my food was dropped in front of me I had a check on the table withour asking if I needed/wanted anything else. After I order another beer, just in spite, my check then delivered with my beer. While this doesn't sound like a huge deal, it's just bad service for the second night in a row. By the way don't call, the waitress flat told the waiter not to answer the phone ... unreal! This place could be rocking right now during the series, but the service doesn't want anyone to stay and spend money.

data.title: It's okay, but overpriced
data.text:
Inside the Ramada Plaza is the Riverside Grille. It serves a nice, varied buffet breakfast (free to guests), and sometimes someone (very friendly) even comes around to ask how you're doing, meal-wise. Sometimes not. I ate dinner there once and the salmon was okay, but nothing to write home about. Unfortunately, it was overpriced for what you got.

There is an odd entertainment, as the hotel has its indoor pool in the same large room as the restaurant, separated by a small fence. So you can watch anyone in the water as you dine. Otherwise, there's zero atmosphere. It's a hotel restaurant, okay?

A bar with loud music is the next room over. The people there don't seem to know what's going on in the restaurant, though they're in the same establishment and presumably utilize the same kitchen.

If they'd lower their prices I could recommend it more.

data.title: Only a potato but . . .
data.text:
We were staying at nearby La Quinta. It was late; we were tired so we opted for "close and quick." Walked over for a beer and light snack. I  was at first a bit put-off by noisy bar scene, pool tables, etc., but took a chance, sat at the bar and ordered a beer and the loaded, baked potato. I  asked that that the "load" be served on the side.  Very pleasantly surprised when plate came with generous potato and small dishes of cheese, sour cream, and what appeared to be freshly grilled, lean bacon that was really tasty.

I was shocked when I asked for check and the potato only cost $2. Went back once more on the trip and same good potato, same low price. Refreshing quality and pricing.

data.title: wood planked salmon was excellent
data.text: my wife also liked the chicken parm - looks of the place can be deceiving.  good location - near several hotels

data.title: huge portions
data.text: Good choices on the menu for breakfast, lunch and dinner.  Very large portions and excellent ice tea.   Servers are very efficient and friendly.

data.title: Great breakfast!!!
data.text: Liked it all....a very comprehensive breakfast with really good fresh fruit! Good scrambled eggs, sausage or bacon, yogurt, toastables, good coffee!

data.title: decent wings and good selection of draft
data.text: Had a late lunch at Dukes -- the bar had good selections of draught beer -- had wings to eat -- they have numerous variety -- had the hot wings ( they would be classed as mild at most places I have had wings before) and garlic -- prefer my wings not too hot - so they were very good and the garlic were very garlicy ( if there is such a word) -- bar had just opened so was very quiet -- will likely return for supper

data.title: Bar food done right
data.text:
We heard about a buffet that included ribs and steaks to order.  This was the first time they had done a buffet so we decided to give it a try.  This was a fortuitous decision for us.  Ribs, pulled pork, cornbread, seafood salad, creamed spinach, fried chicken and steaks to order.  

This was definitely not buffet food.  Everything on the buffet was excellent.  Between the three of us, we tried everything on the buffet.  There wasn't one dish that we didn't like.  The corn with caramelized red onions is not to be missed.

The wait staff did a very nice job and were very prompt with all our needs.

The only concern we had the whole evening was that the steaks were very undercooked.  The flavor was excellent but a medium ordered steak came out rare.  

We will definitely return and order order from the menu.  This one-time buffet allowed us to taste a wide variety of menu items at once.

data.title: Sad to see changes
data.text: I love Duke's, or rather did.  I would have given it a 5 star rating, until this week.  But things have changed. I used to come regularly because they offered food that was different than the standard fare that you can get all over Casper.  But now they are NO different.  They have a new Exec Chef and the changes are disappointing.  Lunch fare is the same burgers and chicken sandwiches that are offered all over Casper (and the state for that matter).  Will not be going back.  Rumor has it I won't be able to anyway as they are said not to be offering a lunch menu pretty soon.  Wish the restaurant community in Casper could see the opportunity they are missing out there.  Not everyone wants hamburgers every day.

data.title: Good Food. Good Price.
data.text: I didn't want to drive outside in the cold so I had a lunch twice. The food was good (quality and portions) and they had some good healthy choices for sides. I would recommend the panini and the rib-eye burger.

data.title: Great Combination of Bar/Grill OR Restaurant
data.text:
This is an unusual combination of a very good bar and grill with multiple screens for sports fans inside a motel venue (the Ramada Inn) with a separate restaurant sharing the same kitchen but separate menus. I wanted to watch the Sunday afternoon NFL game without the noise of a sports bar. I was seated in the restaurant and found the prices to be more than I wanted to pay for dinner ($15-$25), but was allowed to order off of the bar and grill menu while also enjoying the restaurant salad bar. Nice combination!

The salad bar is a little higher than basic, but fresh and well stocked. The $10 cheese steak sandwhich had a large portion of meat and cheese with more onion rings than I could eat, served with horseradish, lettuce, tomattoes, pickles, etc. It was a very generous portion for the money. 

Generally I do not go to a motel restaurant and/or bar and grill. Because I stayed at the Ramada, I gave this a try. Glad I did and will return when in Casper.

data.title: Great wings
data.text: The happy hour featured fifty cent wings, and half priced sides., I ordered 12 wings, and a plate of sweet potato fries. I should have just ordered half orders! The wings were huge, and the order of fries could feed two people. The bar staff was efficient,but very friendly. One of the better meals enjoyed on my trip.
